urls.title: More SARS-CoV-2 variants have emerged from immunocompromised hosts, shows research
urls.description: A number of SARS-CoV-2 variants have emerged from immunocompromised hosts, research has identified. It is thought that variants of concern - including B.1.1.7, a variant first identified in Kent - were a result of long-term infection in people with a weakened immune system.
